\n\n

The workshop is organized by

the “Mössbauer collaboration at ISOLDE/CERN”. This group has for many years applied implantation short lived radioactive parent isotopes produced at the large-scale facility of ISOLDE at CERN for emission Mössbauer spectroscopy mostly in the field of material sciences.

The aim of the workshop is to summarize the main findings of the collaboration in the recent years, with the main objective to bring together groups potentially interested in making use of emission Mössbauer spectroscopy for studies in material sciences and/or biophysics. A focus is also dedicated to introduce the possibilities available at ISOLDE/CERN to worldwide groups already using emission Mössbauer spectroscopy in different research
fields.

Within the next decade, ISOLDE will undergo a major upgrade (the HIE-ISOLDE), which is expected to result in higher

intensity beams and more flexibility, making available new possibilities of applying emission Mössbauer spectroscopy.

Contacts:

Local organizer: Alberta Bonanni 

Abstracts/Information/Registration: Haraldur P. Gunnlaugsson

Registration is free, but we appriciate letting us know for logistic purposes
